      "choices": [
        {
          "id": 13999,
          "text": "<p><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\">Prevalence = Incidence / Duration</span></span></p>"
        },
        {
          "id": 14000,
          "text": "<p><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\">Prevalence = Incidence x Duration</span></span></p>"
        },
        {
          "id": 14001,
          "text": "<p><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\">Prevalence = Incidence + Duration</span></span></p>"
        },
        {
          "id": 14002,
          "text": "<p><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\">Prevalence = Duration / Incidence</span></span></p>"
        }
      ],
      "text": "<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Calibri&quot;,sans-serif\">A 45-year-old public health researcher is analyzing data from a small isolated island community where no migration has occurred for many years. The researcher is interested in understanding the prevalence of a chronic disease in this community. He recalls a formula that relates incidence and duration to prevalence, especially in stable populations where migration is not a concern. Under these conditions, how is prevalence best described?</span></span></p>",
      "unique_key": "Q1369501",
      "question_audio": null,
      "question_video": null,
      "map_id": 34049,
      "difficulty_level": "beginner",
      "subjects_id": [
        7
      ],
      "solution": "<p><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><strong>Ans. B. Prevalence = Incidence x Duration</strong></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><strong>Option B:</strong></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n\t<li><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><strong>Prevalence</strong> is a <strong>Proportion</strong> (Total=New + Old Cases): <strong>Numerator</strong> is a part of <strong>denominator</strong>, and is always expressed in percentage</span></span>\r\n\r\n\t<ul>\r\n\t\t<li><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><strong>Point Prevalence</strong> is defined as the <strong>number of total cases</strong> at a given point in time</span></span></li>\r\n\t\t<li><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><strong>Period prevalence</strong> is defined by the <strong>number of total cases in a given year</strong></span></span></li>\r\n\t</ul>\r\n\t</li>\r\n\t<li><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><strong>Prevalence </strong>describes the <strong>balance between incidence,</strong> <strong>mortality, and recovery</strong></span></span></li>\r\n\t<li><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><strong>Prevalence</strong> can be determined from - <strong>Cross-Sectional Study</strong></span></span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><strong><u>Educational Objective</u></strong><strong>:</strong></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><strong>Relationship between Incidence and Prevalence</strong>: Given the <strong>assumption that population</strong> is <strong>stable </strong>AND incidence &amp; duration are unchanging, </span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><strong>Prevalence = Incidence &times; Mean duration of the disease </strong></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\">P = I &times; d</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><strong><u>Ref</u></strong><strong>: Park 26<sup>th</sup> ed pg 69</strong></span></span></p>",
