      "text": "<p style=\"text-align:justify;\"><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt;\">In an ongoing discussion about epidemiological measures, a group of public health professionals are deliberating on the characteristics of prevalence. Which of the following statements about prevalence is not accurate?</span></p>",
      "unique_key": "Q8650577",
      "question_audio": null,
      "question_video": null,
      "map_id": 34051,
      "difficulty_level": "difficult",
      "subjects_id": [
        7
      ],
      "solution": "<p><span style=\"font-size:16px;\"><strong>Ans. B. It is rate</strong></span></p><p>&nbsp;</p><p><span style=\"font-size:16px;\"><strong>Option B.</strong></span></p><p>&nbsp;</p><p><span style=\"font-size:16px;\">The term <strong>“disease prevalence”</strong> refers specifically to all <strong>current cases</strong> (old and new) existing at a given <strong>point in time</strong>, or over a <strong>period of time in a given population</strong>. Although referred to as a rate, prevalence rate is really a proportion.</span></p><p>&nbsp;</p><p><span style=\"font-size:16px;\"><strong>Other Options:</strong></span></p><p>&nbsp;</p><p><span style=\"font-size:16px;\"><strong>Option A. It reflects both new and existing cases</strong>: Correct. This is what distinguishes prevalence from incidence.</span></p><p>&nbsp;</p><p><span style=\"font-size:16px;\"><strong>Option C. It is a type of proportion</strong>: Correct. Prevalence is mathematically a proportion, not a rate, as it lacks a time component in the denominator.</span></p><p>&nbsp;</p><p><span style=\"font-size:16px;\"><strong>Option D. It is affected by the duration of disease:</strong> Correct. Chronic diseases with long duration (e.g., diabetes, asthma) tend to have high prevalence even with low incidence.</span></p><p>&nbsp;</p><p><span style=\"font-size:16px;\"><strong><u>Educational Objective:</u></strong></span></p><p>&nbsp;</p><p style=\"text-align:justify;\"><span style=\"font-size:16px;\"><img src=\"https://cerebellum-web-static.s3.amazonaws.com/media/public/images/2023/07/05/image-20230705143850-1.png\" width=\"524\" height=\"61\"></span></p><p style=\"text-align:justify;\">&nbsp;</p><p style=\"text-align:justify;\"><span style=\"font-size:16px;\"><strong><u>Ref</u>: Park 26th ed 69</strong></span></p>",
